## 3. Ideogram

**Website:** https://ideogram.ai/

Ideogram is bijzonder goed in tekst rendering - perfect voor REAPER UI met leesbare labels.

### Prompt 1: REAPER Track Control Panel Detail

```
Detailed view of REAPER DAW Track Control Panel, dark grey theme. Shows 4 tracks stacked vertically with exact labels: "Vocals" with red color bar, "Drums" with blue color bar, "Bass" with purple color bar, "Other" with green color bar. Each track shows: track name text, M S R buttons (Mute Solo Record), volume fader, pan knob. Small VU meters showing activity. Font is small sans-serif. To the right, partial view of arrange area with matching colored waveforms. Photorealistic software screenshot, authentic REAPER interface style.
```

### Prompt 2: Stemperator Menu in REAPER

```
Screenshot of REAPER DAW showing right-click context menu. Dark grey interface. Menu shows hierarchical structure: "Item processing" > "Stemperator" submenu expanded showing options: "AI Stem Separation...", "Quick: Karaoke", "Quick: Vocals Only", "Quick: Drums Only", "Quick: Bass Only", "Quick: All Stems". Each menu item has proper spacing and hover highlight. Background shows arrange view with audio waveform. Realistic Windows/Linux application menu styling. Clear readable text.
```

### Prompt 3: REAPER Toolbar Icons Close-up

```
Extreme close-up of REAPER custom toolbar, dark grey background. Row of 10 square buttons (30x30 pixels each) with icons and labels below: gear icon "Setup", microphone "Vocals", drum "Drums", bass guitar "Bass", electric guitar "Guitar", piano "Piano", waveform "Other", grid "4-Stem", grid "6-Stem", layers "Explode". Icons have subtle color tints matching stem colors (red, blue, purple, orange, pink, green). Clean flat design, slight button borders. Text labels in small sans-serif font below each icon.
```

### Prompt 4: REAPER Project met Stemperator Resultaat

```
Full REAPER DAW interface screenshot, dark grey default theme. Top: transport bar with play/stop buttons, time display showing "2:34.567", tempo "120 BPM". Left: Track Control Panel showing 5 tracks - "Mix (Original)" muted, "Vocals", "Drums", "Bass", "Other" with colored indicators. Center: Arrange view with horizontal waveforms, the original grey/muted, stems in red, blue, purple, green. Timeline ruler showing bars 1-16. Bottom: Mixer panel with 4 visible channel strips. Right edge: Media Explorer collapsed. Authentic REAPER v7 appearance, photorealistic.
